node.text:
2020 Elk Season Highlights [30 of 30]:⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Elk Season 2020 will likely go down as one of the tougher elk hunting seasons we can remember. The rut seemed subdued - it seemed to start late and end early. Fires and smoke, extreme heat and dry conditions, and multiple other factors contributed to consistent frustrations. But, in every hardship, there came renewed determination and rewards for persistence.⁠⠀
*⁠⠀
Destination Elk V3 will be kicking off within the pages of the University of Elk Hunting Online Course for all active Members in January, and we'll be bringing the full release to everyone else during the summer months leading up to elk season.⁠⠀
*⁠⠀
We'll be bringing you a total of 9 successful elk hunts - and the lessons learned from several additional unsuccessful days - in the raw style you've become accustomed to. A total of nearly 30 episodes will make up this season's Destination Elk series, and we can't wait to kick it off and share it with you!⁠⠀
*⁠⠀
If you're not already a member of the University of Elk Hunting, you can sign up today using the code DEV3 to save $30! This is our biggest discount of the year, and it's for a very limited time. Sign up today, and be the first to see the entire season of Destination Elk V3, as well as have opportunities to win some awesome gear. ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
#universityofelkhunting #destinationelkV3 #elk101 #elkhunting #elkseason⁠⠀

node.text:
Do you like elk hunting? Do you want to hunt elk with Corey Jacobsen during the peak of the rut this fall? Here is your chance!

Elk101 has teamed up with our good friends @mtnops to bring you the #ultimateelkhunt giveaway! One lucky winner is going to be going on an all expense paid 5 day Elk Hunt this fall with Corey Jacobsen!

For all the details, and to get entered, click the link in our bio!

#UltimateElkHunt #elk101 #ElkHunting #Elk #ConquerMore #DestinationElk

node.text: Corey and Donnie from Elk 101 joined the @workingclassbowhunter to discuss elk, Elk 101, and The University Of Elk Hunting! They also get to some listener Patreon exclusive questions. Check it out today! #elk101 #workingclassbowhunter #podcast #elkhunting

node.text: You’ve finally got all the meat back to the truck. Now what? Is it off to the processor or do you process your own meat? If you do process it yourself, what do you do with the meat? #elk101 #elkhunting #elk101success #meatprocessing

node.text:
Destination Elk V4 kicks off this week! Are You Ready???

*

@coreyjacobsen.elk101 and @eatsleephuntelk are back, and this season’s Destination Elk video series is going to be bigger and better than ever! #DEV4 begins filming later this week, and @Elk101 is going to be bringing you an incredible lineup of Elk Hunters and Elk Hunting Destinations for this season’s series.

*

DEV4 will include exciting elk hunts from Idaho, Montana, Wyoming, Oregon, and….ALASKA! Yep, you heard correctly – Corey and Donnie will be travelling to the Last Frontier to see if they can get the Roosevelt Elk monkey off their backs! This is sure to be one of their most incredible elk hunting adventures yet.

*

In addition to following along with Corey and Donnie, familiar faces such as twin brothers Mark and Jeff Skousen (@skousenbroslive ) and Angry Spike’s Shannon Mobbs and Cory Ford (@angryspikeproductions ) will once again be part of the action. But that’s not all…

*

Destination Elk V4 is going to bring a brand new format that will include 7 Teams hunting elk in 5 States for 8 Days in the middle of the rut, and each episode will bring you daily action from each camp. What team are you betting on to get it done this season?

*

#Elk101 #DestinationElk #DEV4 #Elk #ElkHunting #ElkCalls

node.text:
"The University of Elk Hunting Online Course taught me a lot throughout the course, but the main thing I took was to be more aggressive with calling and getting in close. Might not have been the herd bull but this satellite just had to come check us out and I was ready. After eight days, I was able to make a 30 yard frontal shot (which I learned a lot about in the course as well and gave me the confidence in that shot). Big thanks to Corey for teaching me about calling and elk behavior and how to set up. Couldn’t have gotten my first archery bull without it."

-Colby Keisel

Thank you for the kind words Colby, and congratulations! Great shot!!! #testimonialthursday #universityofelkhunting #elk101 #elkhunting #elk101success
